There is a very obscure passage in Quintilian VIII. 3, § 25, with regard to this word; “Satis est vetus: quid necesse est, quaeso, dicere oppido? quo sunt usi paululum tempore nostro superiores: vereor ut iam nos ferat quisquam.” Are we to understand that Quin- tilian here condemns altogether the use of the word oppido, or that he merely disapproves of the use of oppido in the sense of saus, or does he mean something different from either of these explanations?
